Less than 24 hours after publishers announced a July 16 release date for ``Harry Potter and the Half Blood Prince'' _British author J.K. Rowling's sixth novel set in the halls of Hogwarts School of Witchcraft and Wizardry_ it had shot to No. 1 on online bookseller amazon.co.uk's Hot 100 book list. ``The fact that the book has already hit No. 1 in our Hot 100 books chart shows how incredibly excited customers are about the sixth Harry Potter,'' amazon.co.uk managing director Robin Terrell said. The company was expecting a similar response for the latest installment. 